Kauder Wants Transaction Tax Even Without U.S., U.K., Welt Says

-- B y   S h e e n a g h   M a t t h e w s
-- 
2011-10-22T12:36:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-22/kauder-wants-transaction-tax-even-without-u-s-u-k-welt-says.html
Volker Kauder , the floor leader for
German Chancellor  Angela Merkel ’s Christian Democrats, wants a
financial transaction tax in the eurozone even if the U.S. and
U.K. don’t introduce one, he said in a guest commentary in  Welt
am Sonntag .  Other measures are also needed to decelerate trading,
Kauder said in an article to be published in tomorrow’s edition
of the German newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sheenagh Matthews in Frankfurt at 
 smatthews6@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Benedikt Kammel at 
 bkammel@bloomberg.net  